PME is the patient matching engine, and it follows the rules

187
00:10:50.404 --> 00:10:51.364
engine. We are

188
00:10:52.464 --> 00:10:55.844
in early stages of pilot to utilize the

189
00:10:56.104 --> 00:10:59.524
eligibility criteria I mentioned on the previous screen.

190
00:11:00.024 --> 00:11:03.764
Can we use MCPs and other matching tools to

191
00:11:03.824 --> 00:11:07.024
match patients to studies to streamline the

192
00:11:07.324 --> 00:11:08.104
process?

193
00:11:09.844 --> 00:11:13.204
And as you can see at the bottom, there are two

194
00:11:13.804 --> 00:11:17.284
verification by human steps purposely

195
00:11:17.294 --> 00:11:20.854
designed. Initial humans review, and there is a verification

