00:11:41.264 --> 00:11:41.484
Tena?

203
00:11:48.804 --> 00:11:52.704
Okay. So, this slide, this is how

204
00:11:52.744 --> 00:11:56.664
we represent the roadmap that we're looking for into the

205
00:11:56.704 --> 00:11:58.184
future. So this particular

206
00:11:59.356 --> 00:12:03.056
Roadmap is based on the ARTIE initiative, AI for Research or

207
00:12:03.116 --> 00:12:07.076
Translational Informatics. And what you see here

208
00:12:07.196 --> 00:12:10.756
are areas where we've identified we could

209
00:12:10.896 --> 00:12:14.676
use technology to modernize certain

210
00:12:14.736 --> 00:12:18.376
operations within these areas. And so you can see many of the

211
00:12:18.796 --> 00:12:22.776
topics here relate to the study teams and how they develop

212
00:12:22.796 --> 00:12:25.056
their protocols and how they start

213
00:12:26.316 --> 00:12:29.996
conducting their protocols even through study closeout and then data

214
00:12:30.096 --> 00:12:33.896
sharing. But an important piece to note on here is the patient

215
00:12:33.996 --> 00:12:37.976
aspect, and you see that down at the bottom, where we are also

216
00:12:37.996 --> 00:12:41.336
developing tools that help patients,

217
00:12:41.776 --> 00:12:45.676
once they're diagnosed, to help identify trials that they may

218
00:12:46.996 --> 00:12:50.836
qualify for, and then referring those patients to the right study

219
00:12:50.936 --> 00:12:54.876
teams, and then also providing an educational feature

220
00:12:54.936 --> 00:12:56.946
that uses more modern techniques,

